  "texts": [
    "This file encompasses detailed information about every registered voter, obtained by merging public information with commercial data.",
    "They field surveys during the campaign to obtain timely information about voting behaviour for the upcoming election, and merge these with the VR files.",
    "Using this augmented dataset, they deploy ML algorithms to generate a series of 'scores', tagging each voter with a propensity to vote, and their probability of voting for the campaign's candidate.",
    "These scores are then aggregated up to a very small area-e.g., post-code or precinct-to inform the campaign's activities.",
    "Examples of this practice are discussed by Nickerson and Rogers (2014); Ghitza and Gelman (2020)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Examples of this practice are discussed by Nickerson and Rogers (2014); Ghitza and Gelman (2020)."
  ]
}